n molecules is comparable with\nthermal energy and Coulomb interaction. Eventually, phase separation of the\nbulk electrolyte into ionic layers emerges once the molecular repulsion becomes\ndominant. Our framework predicts the exact phase boundaries between these three\nphases as function of temperature, dielectricity and ion-sizes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 20:26:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2022 10:43:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-30"}
