odulus imply improved bounds on the Lipschitz\nextension moduli of various classical spaces. In particular, we deduce an\nimproved bound on $e(\\ell_p^n)$ when $p>2$ that resolves a conjecture of\nBrudnyi and Brudnyi, and prove that $e(\\ell_\\infty^n)\\asymp{\\sqrt{n}}$, which\nis the first time that the order of $e(X)$ has been evaluated for any normed\nspace $X$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 21:14:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Dec 2021 14:07:36 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 30 Dec 2021 13:10:59 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 19 Mar 2022 12:05:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-22"}
